<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="261" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/8–343</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Assistant to the President’s Military
                                    Aide</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hammond</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-03">August 3,
                                    1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p rend="center">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the Secretary of State</hi>
                            </p>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>The following message from Admiral Leahy was received in the
                                    White House Map Room this date: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“Please inform General Marshall and State Department that
                                            the President approves in principle <gloss target="#t_White1">
                                                <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                                            </gloss> Number 25<note n="1" xml:id="d261fn1">i.e., the
                                                conditions enclosed with Marshall’s memorandum of
                                                August 2, 1943, to Hull, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_530">p.
                                                530</ref>.</note> but that Ave must be very sure of
                                            the inspection if these terms are accepted.”</p>
                                    </quote>
                                </item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>General Marshall has been informed of the above message.<note n="2" xml:id="d261fn2">Hull was informed on August 3, 1943,
                                        by the Secretary of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (Deane) that
                                        the latter had informed the British Staff Mission in
                                        Washington of Roosevelt’s approval of the proposed
                                        conditions for declaring Rome an open city (740.0011 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/8–343).</note>
                                </item>
                                <pb facs="0665" n="551" xml:id="pg_551"/>
                                <label>3.</label>
                                <item>For your information, a copy of <gloss target="#t_White1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                                    </gloss> Number 25 is attached hereto.</item>
                            </list>
                            <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chester Hammond</hi>
                                </signed>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Lt. Colonel, General Staff<lb/>Assistant to the
                                    Military Aide</hi>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>